    <umbTextpage id="1075" parentID="1067" level="2" writerID="0" creatorID="0" nodeType="1068" template="1069" sortOrder="3" createDate="2012-12-14T14:49:09" updateDate="2012-12-14T14:55:26" nodeName="Staff" urlName="staff" writerName="admin" creatorName="admin" path="-1,1067,1075" isDoc="">
      <bodyText><![CDATA[<p><strong>Mike Hundman</strong>  <em>Principle Owner</em></p>
<p>Mike Hundman is an experienced business owner and investor. In addition to owning and operating building material stores for many years, Michael was instrumental in the creation of Hundman Hotel Management. This management/investment group built, managed and sold several hotels. These properties included: Holiday Inn Hotel &amp; Suites, Wingate, Holiday Inn Express, Stay Bridge, Ramada and two Country Inn &amp; Suites. Mr. Hundman is the President of Core 3 Property Management of which manages residential and commercial properties throughout Central Illinois and is also the parent company of Core 3 Hotel Management. Mr. Hundman’s extensive business background and experience greatly benefit the management teams of Core 3 Property Management and Core 3 Hotel Management.</p>
<p><strong>Mark Fetzer</strong>  <em>General Manager</em></p>
<p>Mark is the General Manger of Core 3 Property Management and has over 10 years experience in commercial property development, construction, and management. Mark is a licensed Illinois Real Estate Broker and has his BA in Business Administration from the University of Illinois, Springfield. Mark values the relationships he enjoys with property owners and considers himself a partner in helping the owners achieve maximum profitability from their properties. Mark’s background in building and developing help provide expertise in maintaining high quality properties while staying under budget.</p>
<p><strong>Michelle Irvin</strong>  <em>Hotel Manager</em></p>
<p>Michelle Irvin has been employed in the hotel industry for 23 years. Her work history includes both operations and sales. She has experience both with boutique hotels as well as franchised properties. She thrives on exceeding owners expectations on top line revenue and bottom line profits. Michelle has personally overseen hotel renovations, PIP projects as well as new hotel openings. Many of the properties that Michelle has managed have received industry awards and she has been very active in industry organizations, including an Executive Board Member of the Illinois Hotel and Lodging Association. Michelle has also given many hours of her personal time to local charitable organizations.</p>
<p><strong>Rick Roeing  </strong><em>Controller</em></p>
<p><br /><strong>Vickie Wilder</strong>  <em>Accounting</em></p>]]></bodyText>
      <sideText><![CDATA[<p><span>Core 3 Hotel Management’s staff takes pride in each hotel they manage.</span></p>]]></sideText>
